Billings.Masonic Building (Billings, Montana):
The Masonic Building, (referred to by Montana State University as the Broadway III building) is a historic building in Billings, Montana that was built in 1910. It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1986 as Masonic Temple.
It was deemed "significant for its architecture as a good example of the second Renaissance Revival style, designed by the well known Montana architectural firm of Link and Haire.
